THE Netherland based Top Employer Institute has issued an international award to Tanzania Breweries Limited (TBL) as the best employer for the third year in a row, following successful implementation of human resources principle observed and measured by the institute. The award was handled over in a ceremony that was held in South Africa, recently. This is the third year in a row that the company has been certified as an international Top Employer. Managing Director at TBL, Philip Redman said, “TBL is proud to receive this award for the year in a row as it demonstrates our continuous efforts in making our company an employer of choice both locally and internationally.” TBL has been recognized for its exceptional employee conditions and the development of HR practices by putting their people first. The company helps enrich the world of work with through outstanding dedication to HR excellence and because of this, TBL has been recognized as an employer of choice. The annual international research undertaken by the Institute recognizes leading employers around the world, those that provide excellent employee conditions, nurture and develop talent throughout all level of the organization. Apart from international award TBL has won the Association of Tanzania Employers (ATE) -Employer of Year award in 2015 and 2016 and was a runner up in 2017.